description:
How To Impress People --- I think our society is set up to mold us into basing our self-worth on impressing people. How much money do you have? What are your accomplishments? How many girls have you had sex with? (Cont. below..)

I did a followup video on this topic: http://youtu.be/hxsrLAA-Q18 (Definitely check it out, I think this follow up vid is really good.) 

How buff are you? What level of education do you have? How many subscribers do you have on youtube? How sexy are you? How nice is your car, your house, your clothes? How spiritually enlightened are you? And once you think about it.. NONE of that stuff matters.  And the more you buy into that way of thinking, the more you will live life FOR OTHERS, always trying to impress others, rather than living for YOURSELF. There's no reason to impress others. Stop it. Once you start living for yourself, and doing what makes YOU happy.. you will feel fulfilled & alive. That's also when you will find genuine connection in your relationships because you are not trying to impress anyone. You have no "outcome". You're not trying to get anything out of life, but just enjoying being in "the flow".

After the Infinite Waters collab I was thinking- it'd be awesome to film a powerful short video that could really hook all the new subscribers I got to my channel. I went out to film a vid.. and the words wouldn't come to me. And I realized.. wait a second, I'm not making this video because I'm genuinely inspired to, I'm making this video because I want to impress my new subscribers! I had an "outcome". I was a slave to my new subs. 

I ended up scratching that footage.. and just uploaded a video I enjoyed making (the one w/ Shogo). Even tho it was a long vid and kind of a niche topic.. I was happy making and uploading it because it was what I genuinely wanted to do. I wasn't uploading that vid to impress subscribers, or to try to get more subs.

The whole point of doing this "advice channel" is to live my own advice- which is doing what genuinely inspires up within me & talking about things purely for the reason of: because I love talking about those thing. What makes me itch. 

I should never upload a video that I didn't enjoy making, have a good feeling about when after filming, and be proud of. Why? Because I'd be selling out. I'd be doing something for the opinions of others (views, subs, etc.) rather than doing it for the sake of enjoying it.

TONS of youtubers sell out. They make vids based on popular trends to get more views / subs. Or doing whatever it takes to get more views. And before they know it.. yes they might be getting more views & subs & money etc.. but who are they living for? Themselves? Or are they slaves to impressing people? The more you be a slave.. the more you get stuck being a slave as well. And you're rewarded with fame, money, etc.. so it's a dangerous trap. Rather than making vids that YOU love making & are inspired to make from your heart & true passions.

What makes you itch? What makes you feel alive? Do your best to do that thing/s as much as you can in life regardless of what others think. And keep doing whatever it takes to revolve ur life around "what makes you itch". (might take time & come in waves) You will be fulfilled, internally happy, feel good about yourself, will create connections & relationships that are PERFECT FOR YOU, live a REAL life, and money etc. will come to you eventually cus you're such a passionate person doing what you love and hence become really good at it.

This is NOT about being selfish. I hope you are a loving and kind person who treats people equally! This is about NOT doing things just to impress people / doing things to get approval. This is about being true to yourself, your passions, and finding what truly makes YOU itch & feel alive! 

I realized at first making vids with whatever was a blast. But then the whatever thinking became all business- subscribers. fame. money. & i realized i stopped making the pranks for the sake of making the pranks.. and was turning into a business man. Doing the pranks / picking up girls vids initially made me itch.. but then it became business.. and i stopped enjoying it. and I decided my true "what makes me itch" became thinking about all these ideas. I enjoy thinking / talking about stuff like this. It was hard to give up the fame / money of the popular prank channel.. but in my heart I knew it was the right thing to do in order to be true to myself. Perhaps in the future doing pranks / picking up girls will make me itch again.. who knows

description:
While most people are aware of what the ocean smells like, not many know what causes the scent.
 
Anyone who's been near an ocean has experienced the distinct scent that wafts through the air, but what exactly produces that smell?

According to microbiologist Benjamin Wolfe, no single entity within the ocean causes the scent, instead, it's a mixture of different aquatic happenings.  

Three of the primary smell-producing molecules include dimethyl sulfide and bromophenols.  

Dimethyl sulfide is produced predominately by bacteria feasting on dying phytoplankton, as well as coral reefs. 

Food scientists have likened the smell of dimethyl sulfide to sulfur, boiled cabbage and creamed corn. 

Dictyopterenes are a type of sex pheromone released by seaweed that not only contributes to the smell of the ocean, but also to how edible seaweed tastes. 

And last but not least, bromophenols are what give wild seafood, such as fish, shrimp and oysters, their brininess. 

In high concentrations though, bromophenols smell similar to iodine.

Seafood biologists believe it is caused by what the animals eat, such as algae and marine worms, and because of this, farm-raised seafood tastes differently to that caught in the wild.
title: Why The Ocean Smells Like The Ocean

description:
The Red-wattled Lapwing (Vanellus indicus) is a lapwing or large plover, a wader in the family Charadriidae. It has characteristic loud alarm calls which are variously rendered as did he do it or pity to do it leading to colloquial names like the did-he-do-it bird. Usually seen in pairs or small groups not far from water but may form large flocks in the non-breeding season (winter).
Red-wattled Lapwings are large waders, about 35 cm long. The wings and back are light brown with a purple sheen, but head and chest and front part of neck are black. Prominently white patch runs between these two colours, from belly and tail, flanking the neck to the sides of crown. Short tail is tipped black. A red fleshy wattle in front of each eye, black-tipped red bill, and the long legs are yellow. In flight, prominent white wing bars formed by the white on the secondary coverts.
Race aigneri is slightly paler and larger than the nominate race and is found in Turkey, Iran, Iraq, Afghanistan and the Indus valley. The nominate race is found all over India. The Sri Lankan race lankae is smaller and dark while atronuchalis the race in north-eastern India and eastern Bangladesh has a white cheek surrounded by black.
Males and females are similar in plumage but males have a 5% longer wing and tend to have a longer carpal spur. The length of the birds is 320-350mm, wing of 208-247mm with the nominate averaging 223mm, Sri Lanka 217mm. The Bill is 31-36mm and tarsus of 70-83mm. Tail length is 104-128mm.
It usually keeps in pairs or trios in well-watered open country, ploughed fields, grazing land, and margins and dry beds of tanks and puddles. They occasionally form large flocks, ranging from 26 to 200 birds.[7] It is also found in forest clearings around rain-filled depressions. It runs about in short spurts and dips forward obliquely (with unflexed legs) to pick up food in a typical plover manner.[8] They are said to feed at night being especially active around the full moon. Is uncannily and ceaselessly vigilant, day or night, and is the first to detect intrusions and raise an alarm, and was therefore considered a nuisance by hunters. Flight rather slow, with deliberate flaps, but capable of remarkable agility when defending nest or being hunted by a hawk.
It breeds from West Asia (Iraq, SW Iran, the Arabian/Persian Gulf) eastwards across South Asia (Baluchistan, Afghanistan, Pakistan, the entire Indian subcontinent up to Kanyakumari and up to 1800m in Kashmir/Nepal), with another sub-species further east in Southeast Asia. May migrate altitudinally in spring and autumn (e.g. in N. Baluchistan or NW Pakistan), and spreads out widely in the monsoons on creation of requisite habitats, but by and large the populations are resident.
This species is declining in its western range, but is abundant in much of South Asia, being seen at almost any wetland habitat in its range.
The breeding season is mainly March to August. The courtship involves the male puffing its feathers and pointing its beak upwards. The male then shuffles around the female. Several males may display to females and they may be close together. The eggs are laid in a ground scrape or depression sometimes fringed with pebbles, goat or hare droppings. About 3--4 black-blotched buff eggs shaped a bit like a peg-top (pyriform), 42x30 mm on average. Nests are difficult to find since the eggs are cryptically coloured and usually matches the ground pattern. In residential areas, they sometimes take to nesting on roof-tops. They have been recorded nesting on the stones between the rails of a railway track, the adult leaving the nest when trains passed. Nests that have been threatened by agricultural operations have been manually translocated by gradually shifting the eggs. When nesting they will attempt to dive bomb or distract potential predators. Both the male and female incubate the eggs and divert predators using distraction displays or flash their wings to deter any herbivores that threaten the nest. Males appear to relieve the females incubating at the nest particularly towards the hot part of noon. The eggs hatch in 28 to 30 days. The reproductive success is about 40%. Egg mortality is high (~43%) due to predation by mongooses, crows and kites. Chicks had a lower mortality (8.3%) and their survival improved after the first week.
The diet of the lapwing includes a range of insects, snails and other invertebrates, mostly picked from the ground. They may also feed on some grains. They feed mainly during the day but they may also feed at night. They may sometimes make use of the legs to disturb insect prey.
In parts of India, a local belief is that the bird sleeps on its back with the legs upwards and an associated Hindi metaphor Tithiri se asman thama jayega ("can the pee-wit support the heavens?") is used when referring to persons undertaking tasks beyond their ability or strength.
title: Air Gun Hunting Of Lapwing Bird Hunting

Chinna (Sumanth) is born in jail to a convict mother who dies during childbirth. The Jailer (Chandra Mohan) feels sorry for Chinna and adopts him. He brings up Chinna along with his son, Sanjay (Rajiv Kanakala) and daughter. In a dramatic situation, Chinna kills the Jailer’s brother and is put in jail. Upon release, the jailer and his family tell Chinna to stay away from them. So Chinna moves into a rough neighborhood that happens to be under the control of the local mafia there. He overpowers the mafia there eventually and becomes a protector for the people there. A clerk in the commissioner’s office (Charmy Kaur) enters as a co-tenant in Chinna's house. Love sprouts between them. However, she mistakenly assumes that Chinna is a soft natured guy. She's unaware of his reputation in that locality nor of his murderous past. Their relationship breaks when she finally discovers the truth about Chinna. How do they get back together? Why did Chinna kill the jailer’s brother? Will Chinna become a part of the jailer’s family again? All these questions are answered towards the end when the shocking truth is revealed by the Jailer's wife.

description:
Pengamat ekonomi Didik Junaedi Rachbini menilai persoalan Bahan Bakar Minyak (BBM) bersubsidi warisan Presiden Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono (SBY) akan menjadi bom waktu bagi pemerintahan Jokowi-JK mendatang.

Apalagi Pemerintahan SBY memastikan tetap melanjutkan program pengendalian pemakaian BBM subsidi jenis premium dan solar agar konsumsi sampai akhir 2014 sesuai kuota sebagaimana UU Nomor 12 Tahun 2014 tentang APBN Perubahan Tahun Anggaran 2014 sebesar 46 juta kiloliter.

"Ini bukan salah SPBU (Stasiun Pengisian Bahan Bakar Umum) dan bukan salah Pertamina. Tapi salah kaprah kebijakan," tegas Didik saat dikonfirmasi Tribunnews.com di Jakarta, Senin (25/8/2014).

Menurut Didik, salah kaprahnya kebijakan mengelola BBM bersubsidi harus ditanggung dua lembaga yakni Pemerintah dan parlemen. "Indikasi salah kaprah kebijakan publik ini akan menjadi bom waktu bagi pemerintahan selanjutnya," terangnya.

Pemerintah dan DPR sebenarnya sudah mengetahui apa yang harus diperbuat guna mengatasi persoalan BBM bersubsidi. Karenanya, dua lembaga ini harus mengeluarkan solusi tepat dan segera mengatasinya.

Jika polemik BBM bersubsidi dibiarkan berlarut, maka Pemerintahahan Jokowi-JK akan lemah merealisasikan janjinya membangun kedaulatan ekonomi dan membangun infrastruktur.

"Pemerintah baru tidak akan bisa merealisasikan janji-janjinya. Siap-siap pemerintah baru menghadapi ranjau bom yang meledak," pesannya sembari mengingatkan Pemerintah dan DPR mengambil langkah tepat.
title: Polemik BBM Bersubsidi Bom Waktu Pemerintahan Jokowi-JK

description: Nicola Allen gives a quick overview on the research in her lab at the Salk Institute. Allen's lab investigates the molecular pathways that lead to connections between neurons, known as synapses, in the developing brain. Her group focuses on signaling interactions between neurons and astrocytes, a class of star-shaped glial cell. Astrocytes constitute half of the cells in the brain, and astrocyte processes, the "arms" that project outward from the cells, surround the majority of neuronal synapses in the brain. This places them in an ideal location to be actively involved in synapse formation and maintenance and in the modulation of communication between neurons. In fact, in the absence of astrocytes, few functional connections form between developing neurons, while their presence profoundly increases the number of functional synapses.
title: Nicola Allen, Neuroscience

Dental Checkup in Sunshine Coast: Top 5 Food Choices for Healthier Teeth

Dental Checkup in Sunshine Coast: Diet and Dental Health 

Apart from good dental hygiene, a healthy diet is essential in maintaining good oral health. Dental changes happen as soon as you put food into your mouth. Every time you eat, bacteria in your mouth help in the digestion process by naturally breaking down food to sugar. All too often, the same mouth-dwelling bacteria are responsible in the conversion of sugar to acid. Food acid, when left in the mouth for prolonged periods of time, is what causes eventual damage to teeth enamel.

Dental Checkup in Sunshine Coast: Mouth-Friendly Food Choices

Food choices that best promote dental health include food items that protect teeth enamel from damage. More often than not, these food items provide adequate amounts of calcium and phosphorous. Both calcium and phosphorus are essential in the materialization of tooth enamel. This happens when essential minerals are deposited into the tooth enamel after being affected by food acids. 

Other food items that improve dental health include those that have high water content such as crunchy fruits. The high water content of these food items helps dilute food sugars and buffering acids that attack teeth enamel.

Officials still don’t know the whereabouts 43 other college students from the Ayotzinapa teachers college in southern Mexico who went missing on Sept. 26 — the day their group was allegedly abducted by police and handed over to a local drug gang. Authorities believe a mass grave found Monday near a landfill in the city of Cocula may contain their remains, but forensic experts have yet to identify any bodies. 

Fusion this week obtained exclusive footage of the missing Ayotzinapa students joking among themselves as they ploughed the flower fields that have since blossomed. In this video, two of their classmates, Omar Garcia and Gabriel Garcia Sanchez, tell us about the importance farming to the school and why they will never give up the search for their colleagues. description:
At the Lillehammer Games, Norwegian skater Johann Olav Koss dominated the speed skating events. 

First he broke his own world record in the 5,000m. Then he defended his 1,500m title, setting another world record. Finally he won the 10,000m, bettering his own world record by 12.99 seconds and winning the event by 18.70 seconds - the second largest margin of victory in Olympic history. 

Subscribe to the Olympic channel: http://bit.ly/1dn6AV5

As a symbol of respect, the Dutch team presented Koss with a golden butterfly, an honour normally reserved for gold medal winners from their own country.

An active supporter of the humanitarian Olympic Aid project, Koss was chosen in 1999 to be a member of the International Olympic Committee. During the 2002 Session in Salt Lake City he announced his departure from the Athletes' Commission. 

Find more about Johann Olav Koss: http://www.olympic.org/johann-olav-koss
title: Johann Olav Koss - 3 Speed Skating World Records | Lillehammer 1994 Winter Olympics

description:
Toy Story's Zurg thinks he's a super hero. Hulk wants to smash. And we just want to make Play Doh molds! Starring: Spiderman, Hulk, Ironman, Captain America, Wolverine, Thor, Zurg. I bought this toy here: http://amzn.to/IP3AJ7

Mold some mighty friends and save the day! This super-fun Super Hero Squad set comes with molds so you can create the figures and faces of some of your favorite heroes. Roll out some of the PLAY-DOH modeling compound and put it in the body mold to create a figure of the "web-slinging" Spider-Man character. Then, press the molds to create the faces of the "metal clad" Iron Man character and others. Add them to the playmat to complete the action-packed scene or use them to act out bad guy-busting adventures. No matter how badly your heroes get squished in their "battles", you can always make them fresh all over again.

Subscribe so your kids won't miss an episode! Weekly videos :) Thanks for watching, leave happy comments!
